<TITLE> Northern varsity thrash Independent 6-1 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 21 (bdnews24.com)  Rubel struck a hat trick as Northern University came from behind to thrash Independent University of Bangladesh 6-1 in the Inter-Private University Football Tournament at Army Stadium in Banani on Tuesday. Noor A Alam put Independent University ahead in the very third minute, but they failed to keep the momentum when Rubel restored the parity in the 19th minute for Northern. Later, he struck another two goals to complete his hat trick while Johnny, Habibul and Aniruddho scored one goal each for Northern, who lost their first match against North South University. In the day's other match, Dhaka International University (DIU) held NSU to a 1-1 draw. DIU went ahead in the 24th minute with the help of a Robi strike, but four minute later, Imtiaz levelled the margin for NSU. 
